Biscuits — Web

Challenge Description

The application consists of a simple webpage with a FahemSec logo and a button labeled Access Flag, which redirects to /flag.php.

Accessing /flag.php directly returns one of the following responses:

No session cookie found. Please visit the home page first.

Access Denied! You are not admin.

The challenge title “Biscuits” hints that the solution involves cookies.

Initial Analysis

Inspecting cookies after visiting the homepage reveals:

PHPSESSID=...
admin=eyJ1c2VyIjoidW5hdXRoZW50aWNhdGVkIiwidmlzaXQiOjU1NjB9

Decoding the admin cookie from Base64:

{
  "user": "unauthenticated",
  "visit": 5560
}

This indicates that authorization state is stored client-side in a JSON-based cookie.

Vulnerability

The server logic:

Decodes the admin cookie from Base64

Parses the value as JSON

Reads the user field

Grants access if user == "admin"

There is no signature, encryption, HMAC, or integrity validation, allowing client-side cookie tampering.

Exploitation

Modify the admin cookie to contain an admin user.

Payload
{
  "user": "admin"
}

Base64-encoded:

eyJ1c2VyIjoiYWRtaW4ifQ==
Steps

Open browser Developer Tools

Navigate to Application → Cookies

Edit the admin cookie value

Replace it with the crafted Base64 payload

Refresh the page or access /flag.php

Result

The flag is displayed:

FahemSec{b1scu1t5_4r3_ju5t_c00k135_r1gh7?}
